      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a good start for the outline. Can you help me write out the section where i talk about why the \"meritocracy\" argument doesn't really work in this context? I want to show that people who say people just get what they deserve are basically ignoring the facts of systemic inequality. How should I phrase that so it sounds academically sharp and really shuts down the counter-argument?",
